# Line-ending policy: keep YAML (including SOPS-encrypted *.enc.yaml) as LF on
# every platform. Windows core.autocrlf=true would otherwise check these out as
# CRLF, which breaks yamllint ("wrong new line character") and churns diffs.
# CI/Linux is already LF, so this is a no-op there.
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
# Markdown too: docs/lessons.md and others are edited from Windows; eol=lf keeps
# diffs to the actual content change instead of a whole-file CRLF churn.
*.md   text eol=lf
